  <chapter number="5" style="c" sid="1TH 5" />
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="1" style="v" sid="1TH 5:1" />Concerning the times (i.e., the year, day, or month significant events will occur) and the seasons (i.e.,
        the atmosphere that defines the era events occur in; the climate the events occur in), comrades<char
        style="sup">[a]</char>, you don’t need <char style="it">for me </char>to write to you <char style="it">anything</char>;<verse eid="1TH 5:1" />
      <verse number="2" style="v" sid="1TH 5:2" />the fact is that you know full well in yourselves and to a tee that <char style="it">the nature of the</char>
        day of the Lord is that it comes in the same way as a thief in <char style="it">the </char>night <char
        style="it">hits and runs</char>. <verse eid="1TH 5:2" />
      <verse number="3" style="v" sid="1TH 5:3" />When they (i.e., everybody out there) are saying, “Peace and security,” then suddenly and unexpectedly
        destruction and ruin are perched on top of them <char style="it">staring down on them</char> just like
        labor pains <char style="it">suddenly come upon </char>a pregnant woman and there’s no way she can run
        away <char style="it">at that point </char>and escape <char style="it">them</char>. <verse eid="1TH 5:3" />
      <verse number="4" style="v" sid="1TH 5:4" />But you, comrades, aren’t in darkness (i.e., you aren’t being kept in the dark about this) so that <char
        style="it">that</char> day would overwhelm you<char style="sup">[b]</char> like a thief <char style="it">would</char>;<verse eid="1TH 5:4" />
      <verse number="5" style="v" sid="1TH 5:5" />for you all <char style="it">are</char> sons of (i.e., you adopt the characteristics of) light and sons
        of day—We aren’t <char style="it">sons </char>of night or <char style="it">sons </char>of darkness.<verse eid="1TH 5:5" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="6" style="v" sid="1TH 5:6" />So then don’t sleep (i.e., becoming spiritually dormant) like everyone else, but be watchful (i.e., stay
        focused) and sober (i.e., don’t let anything degrade your heightened state of alertness) instead. <verse eid="1TH 5:6" />
      <verse number="7" style="v" sid="1TH 5:7" />You see, those who sleep do their sleeping at night, and those who are drunkards do their drinking at
        night. <verse eid="1TH 5:7" />
      <verse number="8" style="v" sid="1TH 5:8" />But you’re in a state where you’re sober during the day, now that you’ve put on a breast-plate of faith
        and love and a helmet <char style="it">that is the </char>hope of salvation (i.e., of escaping destruction,
        in this context the wrath of God), <verse eid="1TH 5:8" />
      <verse number="9" style="v" sid="1TH 5:9" />because God didn’t put us in a position that’s towards wrath<char style="sup">[c]</char> but <char style="it">He
        put us in a position that’s headed towards</char> acquiring salvation (i.e., acquiring a means of escape,
        in this context from the wrath of God) through our Lord Jesus Christ, <verse eid="1TH 5:9" />
      <verse number="10" style="v" sid="1TH 5:10" />who died for us so that whether we happen to watch (i.e., remain alive and stay focused) or whether we
        happen to sleep (i.e., die) we would live together <char style="it">in the same time and place</char>
        with him. <verse eid="1TH 5:10" />
      <verse number="11" style="v" sid="1TH 5:11" />In light of this, comfort one another and edify each other one-on-one just like you’re already doing.<verse eid="1TH 5:11" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="12" style="v" sid="1TH 5:12" />We ask you, comrades, to know from first-hand observation those among you who do hard work and who have
        stepped forward to stand in leadership positions<char style="sup">[d]</char><char style="it"> </char>in
        <char style="it">the</char> Lord and who advise, warn, admonish, and instruct you, <verse eid="1TH 5:12" />
      <verse number="13" style="v" sid="1TH 5:13" />and to have a superabundant<char style="sup">[e]</char> high regard for them in love on account of their
        work.</para>
    <para style="p" vid="1TH 5:13">Keep the peace among yourselves.<verse eid="1TH 5:13"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="14" style="v" sid="1TH 5:14" />We plead with you, comrades, that you advice, warn, admonish, and instruct the disorderly and insubordinate.</para>
    <para style="p" vid="1TH 5:14">Cheer up those who are discouraged.</para>
    <para style="p" vid="1TH 5:14">Take a strong interest in and help those who are weak (i.e., those who are unwell; worn out with a sickness;
        too physically weak to take care of themselves; powerless to do anything about their circumstances).
    </para>
    <para style="p" vid="1TH 5:14">Exercise patience with everyone.<verse eid="1TH 5:14"/>
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="15" style="v" sid="1TH 5:15" />See that no one, when somebody does something bad to them, retaliates by doing something bad back to
        them<char style="sup">[f]</char>, but instead pursues the common good and the general good<char style="sup">[g]</char>
        at all times.<verse eid="1TH 5:15" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="16" style="v" sid="1TH 5:16" />Rejoice all the time.<verse eid="1TH 5:16" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="17" style="v" sid="1TH 5:17" />Pray incessantly.<verse eid="1TH 5:17" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="18" style="v" sid="1TH 5:18" />Give thanks in <char style="it">the midst of </char>all <char style="it">circumstances</char><char style="sup">[h]</char>;
        you see, this is the will of God for you in Christ Jesus.<verse eid="1TH 5:18" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="19" style="v" sid="1TH 5:19" />Do not extinguish or put out the Holy Spirit <char style="it">when he’s burning</char>. Do not quench,
        stifle, or suppress the <char style="it">Holy </char>Spirit.<verse eid="1TH 5:19" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="20" style="v" sid="1TH 5:20" />Do not despise, treat with contempt, or have utter disdain for prophesy, <verse eid="1TH 5:20" />
      <verse number="21" style="v" sid="1TH 5:21" />but examine all things <char style="it">including prophesies</char> instead <char style="it">and accept
        the good and reject the bad</char> and hold onto the good.<verse eid="1TH 5:21" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="22" style="v" sid="1TH 5:22" />Stay away from any appearance of evil or wrong-doing.<verse eid="1TH 5:22" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="23" style="v" sid="1TH 5:23" />Now <char style="it">may</char> the God of peace Himself set you apart <char style="it">so that you’re</char>
        complete in all respects and <char style="it">so that you </char>meet all expectations; <char style="it">may</char>
        your spirit, soul, and body<char style="sup">[A]</char> <char style="it">be </char>blameless at the coming
        of our Lord Jesus Christ.<verse eid="1TH 5:23" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="24" style="v" sid="1TH 5:24" />Faithful is He Who calls us; He will do <char style="it">it</char>.<verse eid="1TH 5:24" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="25" style="v" sid="1TH 5:25" />Comrades, pray for us too.<verse eid="1TH 5:25" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="26" style="v" sid="1TH 5:26" />Greet all the comrades with a holy hug<char style="sup">[i]</char>.<verse eid="1TH 5:26" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="27" style="v" sid="1TH 5:27" />Make a promise to the Lord to have <char style="it">this</char> letter read aloud to all the comrades,
        <char style="it">so everyone gets the chance to hear it</char>.<verse eid="1TH 5:27" />
    </para>
    <para style="p">
      <verse number="28" style="v" sid="1TH 5:28" />The grace of our Lord Jesus Christ <char style="it">be </char>with you.<verse eid="1TH 5:28" />
    </para>
