      <char style="ft">Spirit—man is a spiritual being, and as such has commonality with all spiritual beings: God, angels,
        and demons. Sin causes the spirit to die; receiving Christ causes the spirit to be born again. The Holy
        Spirit dwells in a believer’s human spirit. Man’s spirit guides him through the course of life.</char>
      <char style="fp"></char>
      <char style="ft">Soul—the soul is the mind, will, emotions. It’s the peculiar things that give a person personality and
        vitality.</char>
